          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1695724881311-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1695724881311-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1695724881311-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1695724884598-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1695724884598-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1695724884598-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1695724884598-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1695724884598-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p><p>Once the dish is hot, add your <strong>free range chicken thighs</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1695724888327-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1695724888327-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1695724888327-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1695724888327-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1695724888327-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> onion wedges </strong>to the dish with the <strong>chopped carrot</strong>, <strong>peeled garlic</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>Dijon mustard </strong>and <strong>chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Crumble in your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
